<sect3 id="sect_definingForeignColumns" label="1">
    <title id="title_definingForeignColumns">Defining foreign columns</title>
    <informaltable frame="none">
        <tgroup rowsep="0" cols="2" align="left" colsep="0">
            <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colwidth="3*"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry rowsep="1"/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Purpose</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>Foreign columns of a <glossterm linkend="browser">browser</glossterm>
                            show fields of a foreign table related to the anchor <glossterm
                                linkend="tableAlias">table alias</glossterm>.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Attributes of foreign columns</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>
                            <figure id="fig_foreignColumnAttributes">
                                <title> Foreign column attributes</title>
                                <screenshot>
                                    <mediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata
                                                fileref="./Screenshots/ForeignColumnAttributes.jpg"
                                                format="JPEG" scalefit="1" width="227" depth="157"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </mediaobject>
                                </screenshot>
                            </figure>
                        </para>
                        <para> For foreign columns you have to define the following attributes:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>the unique <guilabel>Name</guilabel> of the browser column;</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>the <guilabel>Label</guilabel> of the browser column displayed
                                    in the <glossterm linkend="browser">browsers</glossterm>;</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>the name of the <guilabel>Foreign table alias</guilabel> and
                                    the <guilabel>Display column</guilabel> and</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>if the <glossterm linkend="browser">browser</glossterm>
                                    definition is used by a changeable <glossterm
                                        linkend="informBrowser">inform browser</glossterm>, you will
                                    have to define the <guilabel>Browser to use</guilabel>, the
                                        <guilabel>Fill direction</guilabel> and the
                                        <guilabel>Relation set to use</guilabel>. </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Fill direction</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>REMARK!!! Is it really necessary to give an exact fill direction? Is
                            it not sufficient to specify whether changes should be propagated to
                            other groups, forms, etc.?</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Relation set to use</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>The <guilabel>Relation set to use</guilabel> determines which GUI
                            elements would be updated, if a data set has been selected in an inform
                            browser assigned to this browser definition.</para>
                        <para>The combo box <guilabel>Relation set to use</guilabel> lets you choose between:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>local</guimenuitem>, REMARK!!! Explanation is missing!</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>default</guimenuitem>, REMARK!!! Explanation is
                                    missing! </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>relation sets referencing the <guilabel>Foreign table
                                    alias</guilabel>. REMARK!!! Explanation is missing! </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry/>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
</sect3>
